Your project uses **MSTest v3 (3.8.0)** on net8.0. Here's what to expect upgrading to **MSTest v4 (4.1.0)**:

### Breaking changes that affect YOUR code

**`[ExpectedException]` removed** (lines 9, 16) — You have two usages. Replace with `Assert.ThrowsExactly<T>()` inside the test body:

```csharp
// Before
[ExpectedException(typeof(ArgumentNullException))]
[TestMethod]
public void Validate_NullInput_ThrowsArgumentNull()
{
    Validate(null);
}

// After
[TestMethod]
public void Validate_NullInput_ThrowsArgumentNull()
{
    Assert.ThrowsExactly<ArgumentNullException>(() => Validate(null));
}
```

Same pattern for `Process_InvalidState_ThrowsInvalidOperation`.

### Other breaking changes to be aware of

| Change | Fix |
|---|---|
| `Assert.ThrowsException` removed | Use `Assert.ThrowsExactly` or `Assert.Throws` |
| `ClassCleanupBehavior` enum removed | Just use `[ClassCleanup]` |
| `TestContext.Properties.Contains()` | Use `.ContainsKey()` |
| `[TestMethod("name")]` syntax | Use `DisplayName = "name"` |
| `Assert.AreEqual` format string overloads removed | Use string interpolation |
| `TestTimeout.Infinite` removed | Use `int.MaxValue` |

### Behavioral changes (no build errors, but watch for)

- **`TreatDiscoveryWarningsAsErrors`** now defaults to `true`
- **`TestCase.Id`** generation changed — Azure DevOps test history may reset
- Analyzer severities upgraded (new warnings possible)

